	Affectiva seeks a talented Digital Signal Processing Engineer to lead the development of algorithms for our Q Sensor product line.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Develop algorithms that process Q Sensor data (EDA, accelerometer, temperature) for multiple markets (scientific research, life sciences, market research etc.)</li>
	<li>
		Develop both smart and flexible data filtering algorithms.</li>
	<li>
		Implement production-quality algorithms in Affectiva&rsquo;s cloud-based platform.</li>
	<li>
		Detect and extract features from Q Sensor data.</li>
	<li>
		Apply DSP, machine learning and statistical techniques.</li>
	<li>
		Gain deep understanding of scientific and business needs in key Q Sensor markets.</li>
	<li>
		Characterize algorithm performance with real-world data sets gathered from field trials.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Requirements</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		5+ years of practical experience with DSP, algorithm development and implementation. Python, Java, Matlab and/or C++ experience desirable</li>
	<li>
		Solid background in digital signal processing e.g., filtering, feature extraction, time series analysis, and statistical modeling</li>
	<li>
		Track record of success in a small, fast-moving team</li>
	<li>
		Strong problem-solving skills</li>
	<li>
		Active participation and contributions to effectiveness of team, influencing outcomes</li>
	<li>
		Initiates and takes ownership of tasks to ensure team results are achieved</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Education</p>
<p>
	Advanced degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering or equivalent, with significant work in DSP.</p>
